      "comment": "BONUS ETHICS (4) is coming off a 4.5 lengths fourth but in a slick 29.62 at this track over 515m. Can measure up if runs up to latest time. MY IRISH (7) was seventh in a Grade 3/4 two back then in traffic and fell last time at Maitland. Solid beginner and with a good start should have clear running out wide. No luck latest and can bounce back. MR. SPECKLE (6) comes into this as a quickest on the card winner last time at Gunnedah, scoring by 0.8 lengths (24.99). Harder here but will be in this for a long way. RED AURA (8) found the frame here last start and looks a top-three hope again.",
